post_text:
Good afternoon,

I hope this message finds you and your family doing well today. Attached is the LCHS Return to School Plan for the 2020-2021 school year. This document is much like the rest of the world today and is ever-changing. We will continue to communicate with you and keep you updated when things change. The document will be listed on our school website with other relevant information.

Thank you to those of you who have already completed online registration. The deadline to complete online registration is Monday, August 3rd, at 3:00 PM. Student's classes will be inactivated if registration is not complete by this time. Please contact the LCHS Principal's office at 309-697-6271 if you have any questions.

We look forward to having students back in our classrooms, whether it is in-person or virtually. Have a great weekend!

Class of 2020 I am sure you have been going through many emotions in the past few months. You have all banded together to make the most of an unfortunate situation. The entire staff of LCHS wanted to do something a little special for you today on what would have been your graduation day. Today may not be your graduation day but may it be a day to remember all of the remarkable things you have done during your high school career. Through all of the ups and downs, there is still a great deal to be proud of. All of you have made it and accomplished your goal and we celebrate you!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6cI4KEgaF7U&t=6s

post_text:
The Rotary Club of Peoria North announced the recipients of their annual Prescott E. Bloom Service Above Self Award. Nine area high school seniors have been selected to receive the award based on outstanding service to their community and school. Each student was nominated by a parent, teacher, coach or mentor in honor of their commitment to 'service above self'.

This award is presented by the Rotary Club of Peoria North in honor of former member, Senator, Prescott E. Bloom, a man who distinguished himself in the political arena as one who continually put service above self by subordinating his personal wants and desires for the befit of those whom he was elected to serve.

While this year’s celebration couldn’t take place in person, the students will receive their certificates, nameplates, and $250 stipend at awards day at their respective schools.

2020 Award Recipients in no particular order:

Emilee Neisler Limestone Community High School

Great Job Emilee! #fearthelaunch

post_text:
Students and Guardians, please see the attached LCHS Remote Learning Plan for updated guidance regarding your student's education.

We have never been able to do our work as educators alone. We have always asked for your partnership in helping your student succeed. In this extraordinary time, we need your help more than ever to help make sure your student is keeping up their educational fitness. Please be engaged in your student's learning as much as possible.

You can support our efforts in remote learning by:
o Checking your student’s remote learning activities
o Asking your student what they did for the day
o Communicating with teachers if needed
o Asking teachers for their Google Classroom code
o Checking Skyward for student progress
o Reaching out to our counselors for academic and emotional support

Chromebook distribution will be held on Monday and Tuesday from 11am-1pm

Food distribution will be held Monday, Wednesday, and Friday from 11am-1pm.

We appreciate all of your efforts during this unusual time for us all. Together we will overcome!

If your child plans to take an Early College course for the 2020-21 school year, please plan to attend this meeting to learn more about the ICC Early College program.
